; SELECT dead-source elimination, silent-deletion paths:
;  - `dead` is never read, so the RECEIVE of `add` in its clause is
;    deleted silently (add/1 has other live receives, no diagnostic);
;  - `sink` is never read, so its INSERT dies and the orphaned PUSH
;    out of the `mid` relation is silently removed while `mid` stays
;    live through the query.
; The live data through `live` and `mid` must be unaffected.
#message add(i32 X).
#local dead(i32 X).
#local live(i32 X).
#local mid(i32 X).
#local sink(i32 X).
#query get(free i32 X).

live(X) : add(X).
dead(X) : add(X).
mid(X) : add(X).
sink(X) : mid(X).
get(X) : live(X).
get(X) : mid(X).
